<h4 style="margin-top: 25px; margin-bottom: 5px"><li>Do airlines let passengers swap seats?</li></h4>
Yes, as long as both passengers have a issued ticket on the same flight. Seat swaps occur on most flights anyways. Swapping between cabins, such as First Class and Economy, is not allowed, but you can swap within your cabin. If swapping to an exit row, you must meet the needs of the Airlines exit row seating requirements.